# Walkthrough: Robot JOG Continuous Movement

## Problem
Robot jog buttons on GUI needed to provide continuous movement for both Joint (J1-J6) and Cartesian (X/Y/Z/Rx/Ry/Rz) axes. MoveJog only works for Joint on this firmware.

## Root Cause Analysis

| Approach | Joint | Cartesian | Result |
|---|---|---|---|
| [MoveJog(J1+)](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/DOBOT_6Axis_ROS2_V3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_api.py#430-446) | ✅ res=0, moves | ❌ `X+` → -6, `x+` → 0 no movement | Joint only |
| [MovJ(pose+offset)](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/DOBOT_6Axis_ROS2_V3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_api.py#383-398) | N/A | ✅ moves but blocks socket, can't stop | Unusable for jog |
| [ServoP(x,y,z,rx,ry,rz)](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/DOBOT_6Axis_ROS2_V3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_api.py#562-567) | N/A | ✅ moves, non-blocking, stops when streaming stops | **Solution** |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Dobot Nova5 firmware on dashboard port 29999 does NOT support Cartesian MoveJog. [ServoP](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/DOBOT_6Axis_ROS2_V3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_api.py#562-567) is the only viable real-time Cartesian control method.

## Final Solution: Hybrid JOG

### Joint (J1-J6): [MoveJog](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/DOBOT_6Axis_ROS2_V3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_api.py#430-446) native
- Press: [MoveJog(J1+)](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/DOBOT_6Axis_ROS2_V3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_api.py#430-446) — uppercase J required
- Release: [MoveJog("")](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/DOBOT_6Axis_ROS2_V3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_api.py#430-446) — immediate stop
- 200ms minimum hold enforced

### Cartesian (X/Y/Z/Rx/Ry/Rz): [ServoP](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/DOBOT_6Axis_ROS2_V3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_api.py#562-567) streaming
- Press: Start QTimer at 33ms interval (30Hz)
- Each tick: [ServoP(target ± 0.5mm)](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/DOBOT_6Axis_ROS2_V3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_api.py#562-567) for XYZ, `±0.2°` for rotation
- Speed: ~15mm/s continuous
- Release: Stop QTimer → no more ServoP commands → robot stops instantly
- Target initialized from `cartesian_pose_` cache (polled every 500ms)

## Files Modified

### [robot_controller.hpp](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/unified_control_gui/include/unified_control_gui/robot_controller.hpp)
- Added `servo_p.hpp` include and `servo_p_client_`
- Added [sendCartesianStep()](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/unified_control_gui/src/robot_controller.cpp#298-318) slot
- Added `jog_cart_idx_`, `jog_cart_positive_`, `jog_cart_target_[6]` state

### [robot_controller.cpp](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/unified_control_gui/src/robot_controller.cpp)
- [jogStart()](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/unified_control_gui/src/robot_controller.cpp#246-297): Joint → MoveJog, Cartesian → start QTimer + ServoP stream
- [sendCartesianStep()](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/unified_control_gui/src/robot_controller.cpp#298-318): increments target, sends ServoP request
- [jogStop()](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/unified_control_gui/src/robot_controller.cpp#322-347): Joint → MoveJog(""), Cartesian → stop QTimer

## Verification
- **Joint J1+**: CLI [MoveJog(J1+)](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/DOBOT_6Axis_ROS2_V3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_api.py#430-446) → res=0, robot physically rotated ✅
- **Cartesian X+**: CLI [ServoP(x+5mm)](file:///home/pi/ros2_ws/src/DOBOT_6Axis_ROS2_V3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_bringup_v3/dobot_api.py#562-567) → res=0, pose X: -294 → -289 ✅  
- **GUI test**: User confirmed both axes work continuously with immediate stop on release ✅

